  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave this message to Joel son of
        Pethuel.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Mourning over the Locust Plague
      content: "Hear this, you leaders of the people.\n\tListen, all who live in
        the land.\n\tIn all your history,\n\thas anything like this happened before?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Tell your children about it in the years to come,\n\tand let your
        children tell their children.\n\tPass the story down from generation to generation.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "After the cutting locusts finished eating the crops,\n\tthe swarming
        locusts took what was left!\n\tAfter them came the hopping locusts,\n\tand
        then the stripping locusts,[COMMENT[0]] too!  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:4 '
        contents:
        - ft: The precise identification of the four kinds of locusts mentioned here
            is uncertain.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Wake up, you drunkards, and weep!\n\tWail, all you wine-drinkers!\n\tAll
        the grapes are ruined,\n\tand all your sweet wine is gone.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A vast army of locusts[COMMENT[0]] has invaded my land,\n\ta terrible
        army too numerous to count.\n\tIts teeth are like lions\u2019 teeth,\n\tits
        fangs like those of a lioness.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:6 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: A nation.
    - title: 
      content: "It has destroyed my grapevines\n\tand ruined my fig trees,\n\tstripping
        their bark and destroying it,\n\tleaving the branches white and bare.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Weep like a bride dressed in black,\n\tmourning the death of her
        husband.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For there is no grain or wine\n\tto offer at the Temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\tSo
        the priests are in mourning.\n\tThe ministers of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        are weeping.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The fields are ruined,\n\tthe land is stripped bare.\n\tThe grain
        is destroyed,\n\tthe grapes have shriveled,\n\tand the olive oil is gone.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Despair, all you farmers!\n\tWail, all you vine growers!\n\tWeep,
        because the wheat and barley\u2014\n\tall the crops of the field\u2014are
        ruined.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The grapevines have dried up,\n\tand the fig trees have withered.\n\tThe
        pomegranate trees, palm trees, and apple trees\u2014\n\tall the fruit trees\u2014have
        dried up.\n\tAnd the people\u2019s joy has dried up with them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Dress yourselves in burlap and weep, you priests!\n\tWail, you who
        serve before the altar!\n\tCome, spend the night in burlap,\n\tyou ministers
        of my God.\n\tFor there is no grain or wine\n\tto offer at the Temple of
        your God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Announce a time of fasting;\n\tcall the people together for a solemn
        meeting.\n\tBring the leaders\n\tand all the people of the land\n\tinto the
        Temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God,\n\tand cry out to him
        there.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is near,\n\tthe day when
        destruction comes from the Almighty.\n\tHow terrible that day will be!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Our food disappears before our very eyes.\n\tNo joyful celebrations
        are held in the house of our God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The seeds die in the parched ground,\n\tand the grain crops fail.\n\tThe
        barns stand empty,\n\tand granaries are abandoned.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "How the animals moan with hunger!\n\tThe herds of cattle wander about
        confused,\n\tbecause they have no pasture.\n\tThe flocks of sheep and goats
        bleat in misery.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, help us!\n\tThe fire has consumed
        the wilderness pastures,\n\tand flames have burned up all the trees.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even the wild animals cry out to you\n\tbecause the streams have
        dried up,\n\tand fire has consumed the wilderness pastures."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Locusts Invade like an Army
      content: "Sound the trumpet in Jerusalem[COMMENT[0]]!\n\tRaise the alarm on
        my holy mountain!\n\tLet everyone tremble in fear\n\tbecause the day of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is upon us.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Zion; '
        - ft: also in 2:15, 23.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "It is a day of darkness and gloom,\n\ta day of thick clouds and deep
        blackness.\n\tSuddenly, like dawn spreading across the mountains,\n\ta great
        and mighty army appears.\n\tNothing like it has been seen before\n\tor will
        ever be seen again.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Fire burns in front of them,\n\tand flames follow after them.\n\tAhead
        of them the land lies\n\tas beautiful as the Garden of Eden.\n\tBehind them
        is nothing but desolation;\n\tnot one thing escapes.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They look like horses;\n\tthey charge forward like warhorses.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:4 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: like charioteers.
    - title: 
      content: "Look at them as they leap along the mountaintops.\n\tListen to the
        noise they make\u2014like the rumbling of chariots,\n\tlike the roar of fire
        sweeping across a field of stubble,\n\tor like a mighty army moving into
        battle.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Fear grips all the people;\n\tevery face grows pale with terror.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The attackers march like warriors\n\tand scale city walls like soldiers.\n\tStraight
        forward they march,\n\tnever breaking rank.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They never jostle each other;\n\teach moves in exactly the right
        position.\n\tThey break through defenses\n\twithout missing a step.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They swarm over the city\n\tand run along its walls.\n\tThey enter
        all the houses,\n\tclimbing like thieves through the windows.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The earth quakes as they advance,\n\tand the heavens tremble.\n\tThe
        sun and moon grow dark,\n\tand the stars no longer shine.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is at the head of the column.\n\tHe
        leads them with a shout.\n\tThis is his mighty army,\n\tand they follow his
        orders.\n\tThe day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is an awesome, terrible
        thing.\n\tWho can possibly survive?  "
      comments: []
    - title: A Call to Repentance
      content: "That is why the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says,\n\t\u201CTurn to
        me now, while there is time.\n\tGive me your hearts.\n\tCome with fasting,
        weeping, and mourning.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t tear your clothing in your grief,\n\tbut tear your hearts
        instead.\u201D\n\tReturn to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God,\n\tfor
        he is merciful and compassionate,\n\tslow to get angry and filled with unfailing
        love.\n\tHe is eager to relent and not punish.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Who knows? Perhaps he will give you a reprieve,\n\tsending you a
        blessing instead of this curse.\n\tPerhaps you will be able to offer grain
        and wine\n\tto the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God as before.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Blow the ram\u2019s horn in Jerusalem!\n\tAnnounce a time of fasting;\n\tcall
        the people together\n\tfor a solemn meeting.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Gather all the people\u2014\n\tthe elders, the children, and even
        the babies.\n\tCall the bridegroom from his quarters\n\tand the bride from
        her private room.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Let the priests, who minister in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        presence,\n\tstand and weep between the entry room to the Temple and the
        altar.\n\tLet them pray, \u201CSpare your people, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t!\n\tDon\u2019t
        let your special possession become an object of mockery.\n\tDon\u2019t let
        them become a joke for unbelieving foreigners who say,\n\t\u2018Has the God
        of Israel left them?\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: "\u2019s Promise of Restoration"
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will pity his people\n\tand
        jealously guard the honor of his land.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will reply,\n\t\u201CLook! I am sending
        you grain and new wine and olive oil,\n\tenough to satisfy your needs.\n\tYou
        will no longer be an object of mockery\n\tamong the surrounding nations.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will drive away these armies from the north.\n\tI will send them
        into the parched wastelands.\n\tThose in the front will be driven into the
        Dead Sea,\n\tand those at the rear into the Mediterranean.[COMMENT[0]]The
        stench of their rotting bodies will rise over the land.\u201D\n\tSurely the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has done great things!  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:20 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: into the eastern sea, . . . into the western sea.
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t be afraid, O land.\n\tBe glad now and rejoice,\n\tfor
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has done great things.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t be afraid, you animals of the field,\n\tfor the wilderness
        pastures will soon be green.\n\tThe trees will again be filled with fruit;\n\tfig
        trees and grapevines will be loaded down once more.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Rejoice, you people of Jerusalem!\n\tRejoice in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God!\n\tFor the rain he sends demonstrates his faithfulness.\n\tOnce
        more the autumn rains will come,\n\tas well as the rains of spring.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The threshing floors will again be piled high with grain,\n\tand
        the presses will overflow with new wine and olive oil.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says, \u201CI will give you back
        what you lost\n\tto the swarming locusts, the hopping locusts,\n\tthe stripping
        locusts, and the cutting locusts.[COMMENT[0]]It was I who sent this great
        destroying army against you.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:25 '
        contents:
        - ft: The precise identification of the four kinds of locusts mentioned here
            is uncertain.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Once again you will have all the food you want,\n\tand you will praise
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God,\n\twho does these miracles for
        you.\n\tNever again will my people be disgraced.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then you will know that I am among my people Israel,\n\tthat I am
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, and there is no other.\n\tNever
        again will my people be disgraced.  "
      comments: []
    - title: "\u2019s Promise of His Spirit"
      content: "  [COMMENT[1]]\u201CThen, after doing all those things,\n\tI will
        pour out my Spirit upon all people.\n\tYour sons and daughters will prophesy.\n\tYour
        old men will dream dreams,\n\tand your young men will see visions.  "
      comments:
      - number: 
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
      - number: '2:28 '
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
        - ft: Verses 2:28-32 are numbered 3:1-5 in Hebrew text.
          body: 
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "In those days I will pour out my Spirit\n\teven on servants\u2014men
        and women alike.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And I will cause wonders in the heavens and on the earth\u2014\n\tblood
        and fire and columns of smoke.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The sun will become dark,\n\tand the moon will turn blood red\n\tbefore
        that great and terrible[COMMENT[0]] day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        arrives.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:31 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek version reads '
          body: glorious.
    - title: 
      content: "But everyone who calls on the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\twill
        be saved,\n\tfor some on Mount Zion in Jerusalem will escape,\n\tjust as
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has said.\n\tThese will be among the survivors\n\twhom
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has called."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Judgment against Enemy Nations
      content: "  [COMMENT[1]]\u201CAt the time of those events,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\t\u201Cwhen
        I restore the prosperity of Judah and Jerusalem,  "
      comments:
      - number: 
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
      - number: '3:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
        - ft: Verses 3:1-21 are numbered 4:1-21 in Hebrew text.
          body: 
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "I will gather the armies of the world\n\tinto the valley of Jehoshaphat.[COMMENT[0]]There
        I will judge them\n\tfor harming my people, my special possession,\n\tfor
        scattering my people among the nations,\n\tand for dividing up my land.  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:2 '
        contents:
        - ft: 
          body: 'Jehoshaphat '
        - ft: "means \u201Cthe "
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "They threw dice[COMMENT[0]] to decide which of my people\n\twould
        be their slaves.\n\tThey traded boys to obtain prostitutes\n\tand sold girls
        for enough wine to get drunk.  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:3 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: They cast lots.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhat do you have against me, Tyre and Sidon and you cities
        of Philistia? Are you trying to take revenge on me? If you are, then watch
        out! I will strike swiftly and pay you back for everything you have done. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have taken my silver and gold and all my precious treasures,
        and have carried them off to your pagan temples. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have sold the people of Judah and Jerusalem to the Greeks,[COMMENT[0]]
        so they could take them far from their homeland.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:6 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: to the peoples of Javan.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut I will bring them back from all the places to which you
        sold them, and I will pay you back for everything you have done. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will sell your sons and daughters to the people of Judah, and they
        will sell them to the people of Arabia,[COMMENT[0]] a nation far away. I,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, have spoken!\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:8 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: to the Sabeans.
    - title: 
      content: "Say to the nations far and wide:\n\t\u201CGet ready for war!\n\tCall
        out your best warriors.\n\tLet all your fighting men advance for the attack.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Hammer your plowshares into swords\n\tand your pruning hooks into
        spears.\n\tTrain even your weaklings to be warriors.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Come quickly, all you nations everywhere.\n\tGather together in the
        valley.\u201D\n\tAnd now, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, call out your
        warriors!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CLet the nations be called to arms.\n\tLet them march to the
        valley of Jehoshaphat.\n\tThere I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, will
        sit\n\tto pronounce judgment on them all.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Swing the sickle,\n\tfor the harvest is ripe.[COMMENT[0]]Come, tread
        the grapes,\n\tfor the winepress is full.\n\tThe storage vats are overflowing\n\twith
        the wickedness of these people.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:13 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek version reads '
          body: 'for the harvest time has come. '
        - ft: Compare Mark 4:29.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Thousands upon thousands are waiting in the valley of decision.\n\tThere
        the day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will soon arrive.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The sun and moon will grow dark,\n\tand the stars will no longer
        shine.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s voice will roar from Zion\n\tand
        thunder from Jerusalem,\n\tand the heavens and the earth will shake.\n\tBut
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will be a refuge for his people,\n\ta strong
        fortress for the people of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - title: "Blessings for God\u2019s People"
      content: "\u201CThen you will know that I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God,\n\tlive in Zion, my holy mountain.\n\tJerusalem will be holy forever,\n\tand
        foreign armies will never conquer her again.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In that day the mountains will drip with sweet wine,\n\tand the hills
        will flow with milk.\n\tWater will fill the streambeds of Judah,\n\tand a
        fountain will burst forth from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        Temple,\n\twatering the arid valley of acacias.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:18 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: valley of Shittim.
    - title: 
      content: "But Egypt will become a wasteland\n\tand Edom will become a wilderness,\n\tbecause
        they attacked the people of Judah\n\tand killed innocent people in their
        land.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut Judah will be filled with people forever,\n\tand Jerusalem
        will endure through all generations.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will pardon my people\u2019s crimes,\n\twhich I have not yet pardoned;\n\tand
        I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, will make my home\n\tin Jerusalem[COMMENT[0]]
        with my people.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '3:21 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Zion.
